02:08  PM CO: Vlack, DAR: Gross, Clerk: K Kittel. Attorney Michael Joseph Becker in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Aaron A. Nelson in court w/ Defendant Ryan James Rogers. Attys update Court as to agreement. State moves to dismiss Ct 1 with prejudice. On motion of the State Court dismisses Ct 1 with prejudice. Court informs Defendant of charges, possible penalties and rights. Defendant understands and pleads NC to Cts 2 and 3. Court questions Defendant. Court finds that Defendant has freely and voluntarily entered plea and waived rights. Court accepts plea and finds sufficient facts. Court finds DE guilty of Cts 2 & 3 due to NC plea however, withholds entering conviction of Cts 2 & 3 in favor of DJOC. Court advises DE that bond conditions continue while DJOC in effect. Court reviews DJOC and signs order. 20 days to appeal. Clerk provides DE with copy of DJOC and Bond. Court notes new address and confirms phone.  Adjourned: 2:20 pm.

- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia. Testing upon reasonable suspicion or at the Court's directive. All costs associated with testing shall be the responsibility of the defendant. 

- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, A.Busch.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

If the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bail jumping.
